482
01:01:26,206 --> 01:01:28,340
sitting there
in the tent,

483
01:01:28,342 --> 01:01:33,378
We realized
just how vulnerable raouf
and his friends really are.

484
01:01:33,380 --> 01:01:37,215
Watching them play
these violent video games
on their phones--

485
01:01:37,217 --> 01:01:39,684
At first it seemed
like nothing.

486
01:01:39,686 --> 01:01:42,720
But for these
kids, it's their reality.

487
01:01:42,722 --> 01:01:46,957
It's a reality
that's knocking on the door
right across the border.

488
01:01:46,959 --> 01:01:51,127
Extremist groups
like al-nusra and isis,

489
01:01:51,129 --> 01:01:54,396
They want to prey on
and exploit kids

490
01:01:54,398 --> 01:01:56,831
Who don't have
access to education,

491
01:01:56,833 --> 01:01:59,900
Kids who are
in desperate situations.

492
01:02:03,771 --> 01:02:06,205
When we think
about the people we've met
in this camp--

493
01:02:06,207 --> 01:02:07,940
Raouf's family...

494
01:02:07,942 --> 01:02:10,008
-Ahh!
-Okay.

495
01:02:10,010 --> 01:02:11,342
Ismail...

496
01:02:14,913 --> 01:02:16,847
All of our friends here--

497
01:02:16,849 --> 01:02:19,816
They have chosen
peace over war,

498
01:02:19,818 --> 01:02:21,350
To leave the fighting,

499
01:02:21,352 --> 01:02:23,719
To leave the extremists
like isis,

500
01:02:23,721 --> 01:02:25,854
Who they've even
renamed "daesh",

