503
01:02:45,837 --> 01:02:48,371
to help the kids
here, ismail and his friends

504
01:02:48,373 --> 01:02:51,006
Volunteer at one
of the many children's centers
in the camp.

505
01:02:51,008 --> 01:02:52,874
Very good, very good.

506
01:03:42,319 --> 01:03:44,186
just like
the women's centers,

507
01:03:44,188 --> 01:03:47,055
These children's centers
are designed for trauma.

508
01:03:47,057 --> 01:03:49,123
They provide safe spaces,

509
01:03:49,125 --> 01:03:51,525
Running simple activities
that promote healing

510
01:03:51,527 --> 01:03:54,060
And help prevent children
just like raouf

511
01:03:54,062 --> 01:03:56,395
From slipping
too far behind

512
01:03:56,397 --> 01:03:58,997
Or not returning
to school altogether.

513
01:04:00,499 --> 01:04:02,500
These centers
don't replace schools,

514
01:04:02,502 --> 01:04:05,536
But instead gets kids
ready to go back to them.

515
01:05:59,213 --> 01:06:01,147
after four years
of the war,

516
01:06:01,149 --> 01:06:04,450
The burden of refugees in
countries neighboring syria

517
01:06:04,452 --> 01:06:06,652
Has reached
a breaking point,

518
01:06:06,654 --> 01:06:09,688
Forcing them to often
effectively close their borders

519
01:06:09,690 --> 01:06:12,323
To those fleeing
the violence.

520
01:06:12,325 --> 01:06:15,025
6.5 million people
remain displaced

521
01:06:15,027 --> 01:06:17,694
From their homes
inside of syria.

522
01:06:17,696 --> 01:06:20,496
This is the moment
where countries
all over the world

523
01:06:20,498 --> 01:06:24,199
Need to open their borders
to syrians in need

524
01:06:24,201 --> 01:06:27,235
And to support host countries,
like jordan,

525
01:06:27,237 --> 01:06:29,470
Who have already
welcomed so many,

526
01:06:29,472 --> 01:06:31,338
Yet do not have
the resources

527
01:06:31,340 --> 01:06:33,673
To provide the dignity
refugees deserve--

528
01:06:35,142 --> 01:06:38,043
The housing,
jobs and education,

529
01:06:38,045 --> 01:06:40,645
That will not only help
stabilize the region,

530
01:06:40,647 --> 01:06:43,214
But help save
an entire generation.

531
01:06:45,183 --> 01:06:48,051
The world has been so wrapped
up in the violence,

532
01:06:48,053 --> 01:06:50,553
We have forgotten
that this dignity

533
01:06:50,555 --> 01:06:53,055
Is what creates
lasting peace.

534
01:07:02,131 --> 01:07:03,998
Today is
the last day, but--

535
01:07:06,001 --> 01:07:07,668
We hope that, too.
No matter what,

536
01:07:07,670 --> 01:07:10,470
We will--we will
come and visit again.

537
01:07:39,565 --> 01:07:42,733
No, not at all.
And I think--

538
01:07:42,735 --> 01:07:45,168
Especially--I think
it was in conversation
with you--

539
01:07:45,170 --> 01:07:46,636
We talked about
how there's--

540
01:07:46,638 --> 01:07:48,638
There are good and bad
people in every society.

541
01:07:48,640 --> 01:07:52,508
And that's the same
in the states
as it is here.

542
01:07:52,510 --> 01:07:54,576
Before we came, we had
no idea what to expect.

543
01:07:54,578 --> 01:07:56,311
We didn't know
if we'd be welcomed

544
01:07:56,313 --> 01:07:58,313
Or if we'd booted
out of the camp.

545
01:07:58,315 --> 01:08:00,648
But we've been,
from the very beginning,

546
01:08:00,650 --> 01:08:04,018
Felt like people have,
you know, welcomed us in

547
01:08:04,020 --> 01:08:07,454
And, over time, have become
very close friends with
all of you.

548
01:08:17,298 --> 01:08:19,499
What we've really
come away with is,
you know,

549
01:08:19,501 --> 01:08:21,734
We're not just syrians
and americans,

550
01:08:21,736 --> 01:08:24,136
But we really are
neighbors.

551
01:08:24,138 --> 01:08:26,138
And when neighbors
are in need,

552
01:08:26,140 --> 01:08:29,340
Hopefully they
can come together
and help each other.

553
01:08:31,643 --> 01:08:34,611
it was humbling
sitting there
on that last day,

554
01:08:34,613 --> 01:08:39,248
Being surrounded
by people who have
overcome so many obstacles,

555
01:08:39,250 --> 01:08:42,317
But despite everything,
still have hope

556
01:08:42,319 --> 01:08:45,519
And generously opened their
homes and hearts to us.

557
01:08:48,489 --> 01:08:52,258
We're headed home,
but our friends are not.

558
01:08:52,260 --> 01:08:54,660
On average, refugees
are stuck in camps

559
01:08:54,662 --> 01:08:56,161
For 17 years.

560
01:08:58,464 --> 01:09:02,132
It would be a tragedy
to lose the potential
of this population...

561
01:09:03,367 --> 01:09:05,835
When they are
the solution,

562
01:09:05,837 --> 01:09:08,504
The ones who will
rebuild syria,

563
01:09:08,506 --> 01:09:10,372
Or will work
to rebuild their lives

564
01:09:10,374 --> 01:09:12,407
In countries
that provide them homes.

565
01:09:12,409 --> 01:09:17,178
This isn't just the story
of the millions fleeing war

566
01:09:17,180 --> 01:09:19,647
Or the neighboring countries
who have welcomed them in.

567
01:09:20,815 --> 01:09:23,149
This is a story
about breaking a cycle

568
01:09:23,151 --> 01:09:25,484
Of distrust and violence,

569
01:09:25,486 --> 01:09:27,719
About creating
understanding.

570
01:09:29,321 --> 01:09:31,422
Because, as neighbors,

571
01:09:31,424 --> 01:09:34,324
How we choose to
respond to this crisis

572
01:09:34,326 --> 01:09:36,392
Will affect all of us.

